page.title: 01FRISKNEY INDEX/LANDSCAPE
page.content:
Friskney is a low-lying village between Boston and Skegness, protected from the sea by 4 defence banks to the south. There is a church founded in Norman times and a school founded in 1860. Although the village is fairly isolated and jobs are not abundant many families are moving into the area.
